The graph of the function $y=f(x)$ is shown below. For all $x > 4$, it is true that $f(x) > 0.4$. If $f(x) = \frac{x^2}{Ax^2 + Bx + C}$, where $A,B,$ and $C$ are integers, then find $A+B+C$. [asy]
